  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Top, tail, peel and dice the <strong>carrot[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Peel and dice the <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger </strong>and <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1650388129044-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1650388129044-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1650388129044-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1650388129044-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1650388129044-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong>, <strong>diced carrot</strong> and <strong>diced onion </strong>to the pan and cook for 6-8 min or until starting to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1650388135772-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1650388135772-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1650388135772-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1650388135772-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1650388135772-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Strip your <strong>mint </strong>leaves from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> in 300ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[550ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1650388146228-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1650388146228-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1650388146228-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1650388146228-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1650388146228-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the veg has softened, add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and<strong> ginger</strong> (save the rest for later!) to the pan with your <strong>curry powder</strong>,<strong> tomato paste</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, pour in the <strong>stock</strong> and cook for 3-4 min further or until the sauce has thickened</p><p>Once thickened, add your <strong>blanched peas</strong> with a generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong> and transfer to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> – this is your <strong>vegetable samosa pie mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1650388155969-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1650388155969-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1650388155969-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1650388155969-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1650388155969-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong> and unwrap your <strong>puff pastry</strong> and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a<strong> rolling pin</strong></p><p>Lay the <strong>puff pastry</strong> sheet over the pie dish and trim off any excess (use any excess pastry for fancy pie decorations!)</p><p>Press the edges with a fork to seal the pastry to the dish and put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until puffed up, golden and cooked through</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1650388162211-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
